-- Comparison Cockpit — seed US gold investing platforms (topic = 'platforms', category = 'gold-investing').
-- Mirrors 20260705120000_seed_cybersecurity_smb_us.sql. Idempotent (ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE).
-- Provenance is mandatory per row (source_url/source_type/confidence/data_verified_at);
-- full source-by-attribute matrix at
-- docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-05-cockpit-gold-investing-source-matrix.md, translated into
-- concrete seed values (with a Fable-5 pre-migration review + 12 blocking fixes) at
-- docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-05-cockpit-gold-investing-planned-seed-values.md.
--
-- Candidates (9), spanning 2 incompatible business models: Augusta Precious Metals, Goldco,
-- American Hartford Gold, Birch Gold Group, Noble Gold Investments (gold IRA specialists --
-- phone-quoted premiums, no published price list); APMEX, JM Bullion, Money Metals Exchange,
-- SD Bullion (online bullion dealers — live prices, no account fees). Silver Gold Bull is
-- deliberately NOT a 10th ranked slot — no independent 2026 editorial ranking includes it;
-- buyerGuide mention only (see design doc Urteil 2).
--
-- Heterogeneous-field cost model (Slice-7/8 precedent, zero shared-code change): two
-- economically incompatible pricing models (IRA flat fees + non-published phone premiums vs.
-- live online premiums with no account fees) make a single "cheapest" claim dishonest. Every
-- row seeds `monthly_fee = 0`; the real, non-comparable pricing lives in
-- attributes.starting_price_headline/_note instead. No specColumn/compareRow declares a cost
-- winner.
--
-- Attribution Gate: NONE of these 9 candidates has any affiliate_links row in prod (DB-audited
-- 2026-07-05) — only the excluded Silver Gold Bull does (tracking_status = 'unverified'). So
-- ZERO 'offer' CTAs are possible anywhere on this page; every candidate resolves to 'review' or
-- 'visit', matching every prior slice in this rollout. No new affiliate_links rows are created
-- by this migration — is_affiliate = false for all 9, external_url-only for candidates without
-- existing SmartFinPro review content.
--
-- review_slug is set for the 3 candidates with content-fixed US review MDX (goldco, apmex,
-- jm-bullion); ctaMode resolves to 'review' for those 3, 'visit' for the other 6 (augusta,
-- american-hartford-gold, birch-gold, noble-gold, money-metals-exchange, sd-bullion — no
-- existing US review content).
--
-- account_minimum stores the same CASH-floor numeric value as attributes.min_investment_usd
-- (e.g. Goldco: 3500, not its 25000 IRA floor) — kept consistent with the DB row shape used by
-- sibling topics, even though this topic's specColumn/sortOption reads the attributes copy
-- directly rather than the top-level column.
--
-- Disclosed, not excluded (Freedom-Debt-Relief/Experian/CrowdStrike-Slice-6/7/8 pattern):
-- American Hartford Gold (2023 MSNBC investigative piece + Kiesel Law investigation + a
-- documented markup-complaint pattern), SD Bullion (active false-advertising class action filed
-- July 2025 — no "lowest price" claims repeated), Goldco ($2M TCPA settlement, final March
-- 2026), JM Bullion (2020 Magecart-style data breach, ~$14.8M settlement).

