  'birch-gold', 'us', 'gold-investing', 'platforms', 'Birch Gold Group', 'Lowest IRA minimum ($5,000) + a real published fee number before you call',
  8.0, 4.5, 301, 0, 0, 5000, 0,
  '{"segment":"gold_ira_specialist","starting_price_headline":"Phone-quoted premiums; ~$235/yr average IRA fee","starting_price_note":"No published price list for metal premiums. Birch''s own FAQ page confirms: \"total annual custodial fees typically average around $235 per year,\" with the first year''s fees covered for accounts over $50,000 (both live-verified, 2026-07-05). Itemized setup/wire/storage/management line items are no longer published as a fixed schedule — treat only the $235/yr average and the $50k waiver as confirmed facts.","min_investment_note":"$5,000 (confirmed via live FAQ check, 2026-07-05 — lower than the $10,000 figure some older sources still cite)","min_investment_usd":5000,"storage_note":"Depositories: Delaware Depository, Brink''s. Custodians include Equity Trust and GoldStar (confirm current full list directly).","core_features_note":"Publishes a real average annual fee figure (rare in this segment), education-focused sales process, buyback program.","target_user_note":"Cost-conscious IRA beginners who want to see a real number before the sales call, not just \"call for pricing\" — and, at $5,000, the lowest confirmed IRA minimum among the five specialists in this comparison.","founded_year":2011,"bbb_rating_note":"A+, accredited since 2013, only 10 complaints in 3 years — one of the cleaner complaint records among the IRA specialists.","analyst_leader":true,"analyst_leader_note":"Cited in mainstream comparison roundups (e.g. Yahoo Finance) specifically for publishing its fee structure, a genuine differentiator versus phone-only-quote competitors.","clean_incident_record":true,"review_score":4.5,"review_count":301,"review_source":"Trustpilot","review_note":"Also cited: BBB customer reviews 4.8/71 (separate from the BBB complaint count above), Google 4.7/430+, ConsumerAffairs 4.8/114.","regulatory_history_note":"No enforcement action, no investment-related lawsuit found. Unrelated footnotes: a $500,000 employment-practices class settlement (workplace conditions, not customers) and a 2025 website-accessibility lawsuit (Mitchell v. Birch) — neither concerns metal pricing, IRA handling, or customer funds.","editorial_consensus_note":"Consistently described in mainstream roundups as transparent about its fee structure — a claim that matches its own published $235/yr average, unlike most IRA-specialist competitors."}'::jsonb,
  'official', 'high',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['Lowest confirmed IRA minimum among the 5 specialists ($5,000)','Publishes a real $235/yr average fee figure','Only 10 BBB complaints in 3 years']::text[],
  ARRAY['The lowest confirmed IRA minimum among the five gold IRA specialists in this comparison, at $5,000','Publishes a real average annual fee figure ($235/yr) rather than requiring a call for any number — a genuine rarity in this segment','One of the cleaner complaint records among the IRA specialists: only 10 BBB complaints in 3 years']::text[],
  ARRAY['Metal premiums themselves are still phone-quoted and not published, same as every IRA specialist here','Itemized fee line items (setup/wire/storage/management) are no longer published as a fixed schedule — only the $235/yr average is confirmed','A $500,000 employment-practices settlement and a 2025 accessibility lawsuit exist, though neither concerns customer funds or metal pricing']::text[],
  '{"cost":8.4,"features":8.2,"ux":8.4,"support":8.2}'::jsonb,
  'The lowest IRA minimum here, with a real fee number before you even call',
  'Birch Gold Group has the lowest confirmed IRA minimum among the five gold IRA specialists in this comparison at $5,000, and it publishes something the rest of the segment doesn''t: a real average annual fee figure of $235/year, confirmed directly on its own FAQ page, with the first year waived on accounts over $50,000. It carries a clean regulatory record for customer-facing conduct (only 10 BBB complaints in 3 years) — a $500,000 employment-practices settlement and a 2025 accessibility lawsuit exist but are unrelated to customer funds or metal pricing. Reviewed 4.5/5 from 301 Trustpilot reviews. Metal premiums themselves are still phone-quoted, same as every IRA specialist here.',
  false, NULL, 'https://www.birchgold.com/', false, 'Lowest IRA minimum + a real published fee number', 2,
