  'jm-bullion', 'us', 'gold-investing', 'platforms', 'JM Bullion', '3x Bullion Dealer of the Year (public vote)',
  8.0, 4.4, 2319, 0, 0, 0, 0,
  '{"segment":"online_bullion_dealer","starting_price_headline":"Live online premiums, no account fees","starting_price_note":"Real-time premiums over spot. A cash-discount pricing tier applies for wire/check/crypto payment versus card. Published price-match policy. No account fees. Order minimum $99 (confirm current threshold directly).","min_investment_note":"No account minimum ($99 order minimum)","min_investment_usd":0,"storage_note":"Free shipping on orders $199+ (insured, via USPS/UPS/FedEx). Optional storage through a partnership with TDS Vaults (Transcontinental Depository Services) — allocated, segregated storage, Lloyd''s-insured, with vault locations including Toronto, Las Vegas, Singapore, and Zurich.","core_features_note":"Publishes its own price comparisons against competitors, accepts cryptocurrency payment, buyback program. No in-house IRA custodian — IRA purchases route through partner custodians.","target_user_note":"Price-conscious bullion buyers, especially above the $199 free-shipping threshold, who value being backed by a publicly traded parent company.","founded_year":2011,"bbb_rating_note":"A+, 4.64/900+ (BBB customer rating, distinct from complaint count).","analyst_leader":true,"analyst_leader_note":"Named Bullion.Directory''s \"Bullion Dealer of the Year\" for a 3rd consecutive year (2026), based on over 30,000 public votes (43.5% share) — a community public-vote award, not an independent editorial analysis, but a real, verifiable, named recognition rather than paid-PR.","clean_incident_record":false,"review_score":4.4,"review_count":2319,"review_source":"Trustpilot","review_note":"JM Bullion has been a wholly owned subsidiary of A-Mark Precious Metals (NASDAQ: AMRK) since March 19, 2021 — not \"DGSE Companies,\" a common but incorrect claim found in older content about this company.","regulatory_history_note":"Disclosure: a Magecart-style card-skimming data breach affected jmbullion.com between February and July 2020 (names, addresses, and full card numbers were exposed; sister site Provident Metals was also affected from January 1, 2020). It was disclosed publicly in October 2020. A resulting class action (Newman v. JM Bullion) settled with an estimated total value of about $14.8 million, including a $250,000 cash fund (up to $100 per California claimant) and two years of Experian IdentityWorks credit monitoring for all affected customers. No further incident has been found since, and no regulator action was filed — this is a disclosed, resolved 2020 incident, not an ongoing issue.","editorial_consensus_note":"3-time Bullion Dealer of the Year (public vote); backed by a NASDAQ-listed parent, which some buyers weigh as a trust signal."}'::jsonb,
  'official', 'high',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['3x Bullion.Directory Dealer of the Year (public vote)','Backed by NASDAQ-listed parent A-Mark Precious Metals','TDS Vaults allocated, segregated, Lloyd''s-insured storage option']::text[],
  ARRAY['Named Bullion.Directory''s Bullion Dealer of the Year for a 3rd consecutive year, based on over 30,000 public votes','Backed by a publicly traded parent company, A-Mark Precious Metals (NASDAQ: AMRK), since March 2021','Optional storage through TDS Vaults — allocated, segregated, Lloyd''s-insured, with vault locations on three continents']::text[],
  ARRAY['A 2020 Magecart-style data breach exposed customer card data and led to a roughly $14.8 million class-action settlement','No in-house IRA custodian — IRA purchases route through partner custodians','Order minimum of $99 applies']::text[],
  '{"cost":8.4,"features":8.6,"ux":8.2,"support":7.8}'::jsonb,
  'A 3-time public-vote Dealer of the Year, backed by a NASDAQ-listed parent',
  'JM Bullion has been named Bullion.Directory''s "Bullion Dealer of the Year" for a third consecutive year (2026), based on over 30,000 public votes — a genuine, verifiable community award rather than paid PR. It has been a wholly owned subsidiary of NASDAQ-listed A-Mark Precious Metals since March 2021, and offers optional storage through TDS Vaults, an allocated, segregated, Lloyd''s-insured program with vault locations across three continents. Reviewed 4.4/5 from 2,319 Trustpilot reviews. The honest disclosure: a 2020 Magecart-style data breach exposed customer card data and led to a roughly $14.8 million class-action settlement, resolved with credit monitoring offered to affected customers.',
  false, 'jm-bullion-review', 'https://www.jmbullion.com/', false, '3x Bullion Dealer of the Year (public vote)', 7,
  'https://www.jmbullion.com/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
),
(
