  'money-metals-exchange', 'us', 'gold-investing', 'platforms', 'Money Metals Exchange', 'Best for automated recurring purchases + in-house storage',
  7.4, 4.31, 128, 0, 0, 0, 0,
  '{"segment":"online_bullion_dealer","starting_price_headline":"Live online premiums + own depository program","starting_price_note":"Real-time premiums over spot. Monthly savings plan available for automated recurring purchases. Storage tiers: approximately 0.59%/yr ($16k-$99k balance), 0.49%/yr ($100k-$999k); IRA storage specifically is priced lower, around 0.29%/yr including all-risk insurance — the most aggressive storage pricing in this comparison. No account fees for basic dealer purchases.","min_investment_note":"No account minimum","min_investment_usd":0,"storage_note":"Uses its own in-house depository (Money Metals Depository, Eagle ID, Class 3 vault, all-risk insured) rather than a third-party depository like every other candidate in this comparison — genuinely more convenient, but a structural trade-off worth naming plainly: the seller and the custodian are the same company, versus the separation of duties other dealers offer through independent depositories.","core_features_note":"Monthly Savings Plan for automated dollar-cost-averaging purchases, buyback program, active \"sound money\" policy advocacy (a real differentiator in positioning, not just marketing).","target_user_note":"Recurring-purchase \"stackers\" on a standing order, and buyers who want integrated, lower-cost storage without a separate depository relationship.","founded_year":2010,"bbb_rating_note":"A+, accredited since March 29, 2011; 128 customer reviews averaging 4.31/5, alongside 46 complaints in 3 years.","analyst_leader":false,"clean_incident_record":true,"review_score":4.31,"review_count":128,"review_source":"BBB","review_note":"Trustpilot shows a weaker, more polarized picture (3.6/5 from 236 reviews) — the most divided independent review base in this comparison. The BBB figure is shown as the primary score here because it reflects an accredited, complaint-adjacent record rather than an unverified self-hosted testimonial base, but the Trustpilot split is real and worth knowing.","regulatory_history_note":"No enforcement action, no customer-facing class action found (only a 2021 website-accessibility suit, Sanchez v. Money Metals). Money Metals was a plaintiff (not defendant) in a March 2025 Kentucky lawsuit challenging state sales-tax collection on precious metals — a pro-customer policy position, not a legal liability.","editorial_consensus_note":"Known within the industry for its Sound Money Defense League advocacy work; limited tier-1 financial-press coverage relative to the IRA specialists and larger dealers in this comparison."}'::jsonb,
  'official', 'medium',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['Monthly Savings Plan for automated recurring purchases','In-house depository — IRA storage as low as ~0.29%/yr','Active "sound money" policy advocacy']::text[],
  ARRAY['A Monthly Savings Plan automates recurring dollar-cost-averaging purchases — a rare feature among the dealers in this comparison','Its own in-house depository prices IRA storage as low as approximately 0.29%/yr, the most aggressive storage pricing here','Active "sound money" policy advocacy work is a real differentiator in positioning, not just marketing']::text[],
  ARRAY['The seller and the custodian are the same company — a structural trade-off versus the independent-depository separation every other dealer here offers','Trustpilot shows a weaker, more polarized 3.6/5 from 236 reviews, in contrast with its stronger 4.31/5 BBB figure','Limited tier-1 financial-press coverage relative to the larger dealers and IRA specialists in this comparison']::text[],
  '{"cost":8.6,"features":8.0,"ux":7.6,"support":7.4}'::jsonb,
  'The best fit for automated recurring buyers who want integrated, lower-cost storage',
  'Money Metals Exchange stands out for its Monthly Savings Plan, which automates recurring dollar-cost-averaging purchases, and its own in-house depository, which prices IRA storage as low as roughly 0.29%/year — the most aggressive storage pricing in this comparison. The honest structural trade-off: the seller and the custodian are the same company, unlike every other dealer here, which uses an independent third-party depository. Reviews are split by platform — 4.31/5 from 128 BBB customer reviews (shown as the primary score here) versus a weaker, more polarized 3.6/5 from 236 Trustpilot reviews.',
  false, NULL, 'https://www.moneymetals.com/', false, 'Best for automated purchases + in-house storage', 8,
  'https://www.moneymetals.com/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
),
