  'sd-bullion', 'us', 'gold-investing', 'platforms', 'SD Bullion', 'Largest review base among dealers (read the pricing disclosure first)',
  6.8, 4.8, 222105, 0, 0, 0, 0,
  '{"segment":"online_bullion_dealer","starting_price_headline":"Live online premiums (low-price positioning, self-described)","starting_price_note":"Markets itself on low pricing and a price-match promise; free shipping on orders $199+. We deliberately do not repeat a \"lowest price\" claim here — that exact promise is the subject of an active lawsuit (see regulatory disclosure), and documented customer complaints describe a price gap between the listed price and the final checkout price plus a roughly 4% card-processing fee.","min_investment_note":"No account minimum","min_investment_usd":0,"storage_note":"In-house storage program: segregated, Lloyd''s-insured, with the first 3 months typically free (confirm current terms directly for the ongoing rate).","core_features_note":"Aggressively priced core bullion products, buyback program, IRA-eligible products available through partner custodians.","target_user_note":"Price-focused buyers willing to pay by wire or check (to avoid the card surcharge) and to double-check advertised savings against the actual checkout total themselves.","founded_year":2012,"bbb_rating_note":"A+ (BBB) — no additional rating-agency figure independently confirmed for this comparison.","analyst_leader":false,"clean_incident_record":false,"review_score":4.8,"review_count":222105,"review_source":"Shopper Approved","review_note":"A large, long-running review base (over 220,000 reviews across roughly 9 years per the platform''s own reporting) — but read alongside the active pricing-related litigation below rather than in isolation.","regulatory_history_note":"Disclosure: an active class-action lawsuit filed in July 2025 in California federal court alleges SD Bullion''s \"lowest price\" advertising is misleading and that customers ultimately paid more than at competing dealers. The case is ongoing with no ruling yet — we describe it as a pending false-advertising class action, not a proven finding, and we do not adopt SD Bullion''s own \"lowest price\" marketing language on this page as a result. A separate, resolved 2021 website-accessibility suit also exists. No regulator enforcement action or data breach was found.","editorial_consensus_note":"A standard low-price reference point in dealer-comparison coverage (Money.com among others); the active litigation over that exact positioning is the honest counterweight to include."}'::jsonb,
  'official', 'medium',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['Largest review base among the online dealers (220,000+ reviews)','First 3 months of storage typically free','Read the active pricing-litigation disclosure first']::text[],
  ARRAY['The largest review sample of any online dealer in this comparison: 4.8/5 from over 220,000 Shopper Approved reviews across roughly 9 years','Aggressively priced core bullion products with a published price-match promise','First 3 months of segregated, Lloyd''s-insured storage are typically free']::text[],
  ARRAY['An active (unresolved) false-advertising class action, filed July 2025, alleges its "lowest price" claims are misleading and that customers paid more than at competing dealers','Documented customer complaints describe a gap between the listed price and the final checkout total, plus a roughly 4% card-processing fee','No BBB-alternative rating agency figure could be independently confirmed for this comparison']::text[],
  '{"cost":7.8,"features":7.8,"ux":7.6,"support":7.2}'::jsonb,
  'The largest dealer review base here, alongside active pricing litigation worth reading first',
  'SD Bullion has the largest review sample of any online dealer in this comparison — 4.8/5 from over 220,000 Shopper Approved reviews across roughly 9 years — and offers aggressively priced core bullion with the first 3 months of segregated, Lloyd''s-insured storage typically free. The disclosure to read first: an active, unresolved class-action lawsuit filed in July 2025 alleges SD Bullion''s "lowest price" advertising is misleading and that customers ultimately paid more than at competing dealers, alongside documented complaints about a gap between the listed and checkout price plus a roughly 4% card surcharge. We deliberately do not repeat SD Bullion''s own "lowest price" marketing language on this page given the pending litigation.',
  false, NULL, 'https://sdbullion.com/', false, 'Largest review base among dealers', 9,
  'https://sdbullion.com/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
)
